# Task File Format

Each task file in `tasks/phase-N/` follows this structure:

```
# Task Title

Status: `pending`
Phase: N
Depends on: [dependencies]

## Objective
What and why.

## Requirements
Filled during grilling session with user's answers.

## Implementation Notes
Technical decisions and approach.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Checkboxes for completion verification
```

## Status Values

- `pending` -- not started
- `in-progress` -- actively being worked on
- `done` -- all acceptance criteria met
- `blocked` -- cannot proceed, note the reason
- `cancelled` -- no longer needed

## Rules for Updating

- Only change status to `in-progress` for one task at a time.
- Mark `done` only when ALL acceptance criteria checkboxes are checked.
- When grilling reveals new info, update Requirements and Implementation Notes.
- Never delete a task file. Set status to `cancelled` instead.
- If grilling reveals a new task, create a new numbered file in the phase folder.
